page.title: 08A LARGE FACTORY, WOODINGDEAN
page.content: Jaycee Factory makes furniture for the home.They produce about Â£150 thousand worth of furniture a week and they use 2,100 cubic metres of wood a week and 60 sheets of chipboard.At the factory there are 287 people working,including 3 women.The factory covers 4 acres of ground.Over the course of one year Jaycee make Â£7.5 million worth of furniture.They get their wood from America and Sweden:they sell their furniture to the U.K,America,and all the countries in Europe and even Japan.They have 14,40 foot trailers and 7 cabs so that 7 can be on the road whilst 7 are being loaded.In all the wages paid out over a year by Jaycee,total about 2 million pounds.
